        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 5:21PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 519 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms over
Montgomery, and surrounding areas. These thunderstorms are moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern College Station, Conroe, Huntsville, Navasota,
Hempstead, Willis, Prairie View, Pinehurst, Washington, Panorama
Village, Magnolia, Cut And Shoot, New Waverly, Pine Island,
Montgomery, Bedias, Millican, Anderson, Todd Mission, and Huntsville
State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
